docs.text: another 'independent film' , this comedy , which was brought by miramax for $5 million , is good fun .

docs.text: favreau and vaughn ( the lost world : jurassic park , 1997 ) play mike and trent , two everyday 20somethings on the lookout for women .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: the film just basically follows their plight on the lookout for lurve , and along the way we get to meet some of their friends , see their attempts at chatting up girls , and just basically get a insight into their lives .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: and all of this is great fun .

docs.text: swingers doesn't rely on huge special effects , or big name stars to provide entertainment .
docs.label: positive

docs.text: no , it just has a great script and superb little known actors .

docs.text: the script , by favreau , is great .

docs.text: mike is always missing is girlfriend , who hasn't called him for six months , and every time he meets a girl , he always end up telling her about the ex .

docs.text: the audience feels for this pathetic little man , thanks to the great script .

docs.text: some of his chat-up lines are awful , but he always seems to get the girl thanks to his 'hard man' nature .
